1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4. Nf3 dxe5 5. Nxe5 c6 {This is necessary as black 
can run into problems with other natural moves:} (1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 
4. Nf3 dxe5 5. Nxe5 Nd7 6. Nxf7 Kxf7 7. Qh5+ Ke6 8. c4 N5f6 9. d5+ Kd6 10. Qf7 
Ne5 11. Bf4) 6. c4 {We should be happy anytime this move pops up, because Black 
scores better in this variation! Forewarning though that awareness of tactical 
themes is necessary in order to have the edge.} Nb4 7. Be3 {The most common 
move, if 7.a3 Qxd4 is strong with the idea of Nc2+ to follow.} Bf5 ({Black's 
main point: the threat to c2 seems to force} Bf5 8. Na3 {- a constantly 
repeating Alekhine theme.}) 8. Na3 Nd7 9. Nf3 e5 10. dxe5 Qa5 11. Bd2 Nxe5 12. 
Qe2 Nd3+ 13. Kd1 Nxb2+ 14. Ke1 Nd3+ 15. Kd1 Qxa3 {Would be a lovely finish to 
the game} *

